// r1-server vendored htmx shim
//
// work-stoke TASK 12 ships the htmx + Go templates + SSE index layout.
// Production deployments must drop a real htmx 2.x build into this
// file before shipping — the minimal shim below is a no-op so the
// embed.FS walk and the Go tests still see a file at
// cmd/r1-server/ui/vendor/htmx.min.js (the tests assert the asset is
// served under /ui/vendor/htmx.min.js with a non-zero body).
//
// How to vendor the real blob (run outside the repo tree):
//
//   # Grab the pinned 2.0.x release from the official distribution.
//   # Pin a specific version — never @latest — so the UI never drifts
//   # on an upstream breaking change without a PR.
//   curl -fsSL https://unpkg.com/htmx.org@2.0.4/dist/htmx.min.js \
//     -o cmd/r1-server/ui/vendor/htmx.min.js
//
//   # Sanity check (should be ~47 KB minified, ~14 KB gzipped as of
//   # 2.0.4). Adjust the size threshold as htmx evolves.
//   wc -c cmd/r1-server/ui/vendor/htmx.min.js
//
//   # Optional: vendor the SSE extension next to it so hx-ext="sse"
//   # works without a second CDN fetch. Ships separately in htmx 2.x:
//   curl -fsSL https://unpkg.com/htmx-ext-sse@2.2.2/sse.js \
//     -o cmd/r1-server/ui/vendor/htmx-ext-sse.js
//
// After replacing this file, rebuild the server:
//
//   go build ./cmd/r1-server
//
// `//go:embed ui/*` in ui.go walks every path under ui/, so the new
// bytes flow into the binary on the next build with no code changes.
//
// Until the real blob is dropped, the index layout degrades as
// follows: hx-get polling + hx-sse live updates are both inert, but
// the server-side render still emits a usable session list (a plain
// <a href="/session/:id"> link per row). Operators can click through
// to the per-session waterfall just as on the pre-htmx SPA, so the
// page is never completely broken — only missing the 2s auto-refresh
// and the live event feed.
(function () {
  "use strict";
  // Minimal shim. The real htmx registers window.htmx with init(),
  // process(), on(), trigger(), etc. We deliberately leave the global
  // undefined so feature-detection in any sibling script
  // (`if (window.htmx) { ... }`) falls through to the graceful path.
})();
